(4, 'component', 0, '"<h1>The KCM Orchestra<\\/h1>\\r\\n<img src=\\"\\/images\\/content\\/kcm_orchestra.jpg\\" alt=\\"The Kenya Conservatoire of Music Orchestra\\"\\/>\\r\\n<p>The Kenya Conservatoire of Music Orchestra is the highlight of Conservatoire concerts and is on great demand at corporate and social functions.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The orchestra comprises mainly students of all ages and abilities together with staff members. It performs in at least four Conservatoire concerts each year and also makes a tour every year to one or more towns in Kenya or even outside the country. We have played in Diani, Mombasa, Kampala and Dar-e-salaam. The Conservatoire also boasts of forming the first all Kenyan string quartet. We also have a junior orchestra and a jazz ensemble.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Orchestra is available for hire to perform at various events such as weddings, corporate functions and other ceremonies. Please call The Kenya Conservatoire of Music to make a formal booking for either the whole or part of the orchestra.<\\/p>"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', NULL),
(6, 'component under-construction', 0, '"<img src=\\"\\/images\\/system\\/composing.jpg\\">\\r\\n\\t<span class=\\"construction_text\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t<p>still under <br\\/>composition!<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t<\\/span>"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', NULL),
(7, 'content', 0, '"<h1>Plucked Strings<\\/h1><h2>Guitar<\\/h2><p>click here for more details about the <a href=\\"http://www.conservatoire.co.ke/academics/departments/string/plucked\\">guitar<\\/a><\\/p><p>The Department of String Instruments offers individual tuition as well as group tuition as detailed below:<\\/p>\\r\\n<H1> INDIVIDUAL TUITION OPTIONS<\\/H1>\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\"><li>Violin<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Viola<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Cello<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Double Bass<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Harp (Starting Soon!) <\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Classical Guitar<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Electric Guitar<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Bass Guitar<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Fees for Individual Tuition: <a target=\\"blank()\\" href=\\"\\/academics\\/fee_schedule\\">Click Here<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<H1>GROUP TUITION OPTIONS<\\/H1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Group Violin A: For Beginning Students<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Group Violin B: For Intermediate Students<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Group Violin C: For Semi-Advanced Students<\\/p>\\r\\n<br \\/>\\r\\n<p>Group Guitar A: For Beginning Students<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Group Guitar B: For Intermediate Students<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Group Guitar C: For Semi-Advanced Students<\\/p><br \\/>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Fees for Group Tuition Option: Ksh. 500\\/- per hour. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Sessions will commence once a minimum of 4 participants have registered. The Courses will carry on for 12 sessions after which participants receive a report and certificate of completion. The certificate will only be awarded to participants who have completed the 12 sessions. <\\/p>\\r\\n"', '', '2013-03-07 18:00:00', '2013-03-07 19:00:00', '', NULL),
(8, 'content', 0, '"<h1>The Year 2012<\\/h1>\\r\\n<h2>March<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p><strong>1<sup>st<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\">ABRSM Theory Exam<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>25<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong><span class=\\"tabbed\\">End of Term Concert at Alliance Francaise<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>April<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p><strong>10<sup>th<\\/sup> - 13<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong><span class=\\"tabbed\\"> Workshops and Auditions for the Musical<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>17<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong><span class=\\"tabbed\\">Jazz workshop facilitated by Davey Yarborough<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>May<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p>ABRSM Practical Exams<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>June<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p>ABRSM Practical Exams<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>9<sup>th<\\/sup> - 10<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong><span class=\\"tabbed\\"> Singers Of United Lands Workshops and Concert<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>July<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p>ABRSM Practical Exams<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>1<sup>st<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\"> Orchestra Concert at the Go Down<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>22<sup>nd<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\"> End of Term Concert at the Kenya National Theatre<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>28<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\"> Auditions for the Musical<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>29<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\"> Sounds of Praise Concert at the All Saints Cathedral<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>August<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p><strong>2<sup>nd<\\/sup> - 8<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\">Orchestra Tour to the Coast<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>October<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p><strong>10<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong><span class=\\"tabbed\\"> ABRSM Theory Exam<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>11<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\">Acoustic Alchemy Concert at the Kenya National Theatre<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>November<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p><strong>3<sup>rd<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\">Classics at the Go Down Concert<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>December<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p><strong>14<sup>th<\\/sup> - 16<sup>th<\\/sup><\\/strong> <span class=\\"tabbed\\">Seventeen, The Musical at the Kenya National Theatre<\\/span><\\/p>"', '', '2013-03-08 03:00:00', '2013-03-08 05:00:00', '', NULL),
(9, 'content', 0, '"<h2>How do I join?<\\/h2><p>To join, visit us at our main premises at the Kenya Cultural Centre on Harry Thuku Road opposite The Norfolk Hotel. You will fill in an application form and be assigned a teacher depending on your instrument of choice and your available times.<\\/p>\\r\\n <h2>Does the Conservatoire assess my performance in anyway?<\\/h2><p>The Conservatoire is the representative for the ABRSM examinations in Kenya. The Director of The Conservatoire oversees the administration of all practical examinations. Over 1500 candidates enroll for these international examinations in various instruments each year.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Conservatoire does not offer its own assessment and accreditation. Assessment is quite individual because different students progress at different rates. The ABRSM examinations however provide an internationally recognized certificate for successful candidates. Before enrolling for any examination the student must be given the go-ahead by his teacher.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>There are 8 Grade levels for each instrument after which one can sit the ABRSM Diploma. Each grade takes about a year to prepare for the average student.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>For more information on ABRSM please visit their website <a href=\\"www.abrsm.org\\">www.abrsm.org<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>How long does\\/will it take me to learn my instrument?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The study of an instrument is best thought of as a journey not a destination. It takes at least ten years to master an instrument. In the meantime however you are still playing and enjoying yourself, just that the level of difficulty keeps increasing. Within 5 years, one usually has a good grasp of the instrument.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The rate of progress is also mostly dependent on several other factors: the age at which one begins to learn, how much one practices and the natural ability of the person.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Do I need to have lessons everyday?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>It is never necessary to have a lesson everyday. It is best to meet the teacher once a week or at most 2 times and spend the rest of the week practicing on your own.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>How long will I need to practice everyday?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The amount of practice time can vary from 25 minutes to 3 hours! It depends on the age of the student, the level they have already attained, the amount of time they can devote to personal practice and their natural aptitude. One should aim to practice at least 5 days a week. Children will usually not need nor benefit from more than 25 minutes a day.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>What happens if I can''t make it to my lesson?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>When one registers for lessons, they enter into a binding agreement with the school and the teacher. Lessons missed by non attendance are not made up unless the cancellation was for a reason that the school considers adequate and unless the cancellation was done at least 24 hours to the lesson. For lessons missed for a good reason, the teacher will make up a maximum of 2 lessons per term and the student will be charged for any other.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Can I have lessons in the school holiday?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>It is possible to have lessons when The Conservatoire is on its official holidays. One only needs to consult with the teacher and to pay for the holiday lessons in advance.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Do I sit for examinations?<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Because of the individual nature of the skill, we do not offer standardized examinations. We do however facilitate the Associated Board of the Royal Schools of Music examinations in Kenya. These are entered voluntarily by the student and have 8 grade levels before one can attempt the ABRSM diploma.<\\/p>"', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', NULL),
