(13, 'component', 7, '{"artTitle":"SOUL KENYA 2013 - FINAL CONCERT","artTime":"2013-03-26 20:00:00","artAuthorAnchor":"Timothy Muritu","artParagraph":"<p>DATE & TIME: Thursday May 16<sup>th<\\/sup>, 2013 at 6:30 pm; VENUE: The National Museum of Kenya, Louis Leakey Auditorium; TICKETS: Conservatoire Students and Children Below 12 years: 300KShs. Adults: 500KShs. Conservatoire Members: 200KShs<\\/p>","artReadMore":"<a href=\\"soul">read more<\\/a>"}', '', '2013-03-26 20:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'SOUL KENYA 2013 - FINAL CONCERT', 'soul'),
(14, 'component', 7, '{"artTitle":"Acoustic Alchemy Concert DVD","artTime":"2013-08-23 12:44:01","artAuthorAnchor":"Timothy Muritu","artParagraph":"<p>Acoustic Alchemy 2013 DVD''s are now available for sale at the Main office of The Kenya Conservatoire of Music.<\\/p><p>Come get your copy now while stocks last.<\\/p><p>Each DVD is going for <strong>ksh.1000/-<\\/strong><\\/p><img src=\\"\\/images\\/content\\/acoustic_alchemy_cover.jpg\\"\\/>","artReadMore":"<a href=\\"*news\\/acoustic_alchemy_concert_dvd\\/2013-08-23_12:44:01\\">read more<\\/a>"}', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Acoustic Alchemy Concert 2013 DVD', '/acoustic_alchemy_concert_dvd/2013-08-23_12:44:01'),
(15, 'content event', 1, '{"evTitle":"Classics at the GoDown","evImage":"class=\\"center\\" src=\\"*images\\/events\\/classics_2012_11_03_lowres.jpg\\" alt=\\"Classics at the Godown\\" data-fullsrc=\\"*images\\/events\\/classics_2012_11_03_highres.jpg\\"","evDate":"2012-11-03 19:00:00","evVenue":"The GoDown Arts Centre","evTickets":"300 KShs","evDescription":"<p><a href=\\"\\/images\\/Classics%20at%20the%20Go%20Down%20Draft%20Program.pdf\\">Download Concert Program Here <\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Kenya Conservatoire of Music in collaboration with the Godown Arts Centre warmly invites you to the exciting Classics at the Go Down Annual Concert!<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This year''s event will show case outstanding performances from the world reknown Nairobi Chamber Chorus conducted by Ken Wakia, the Kenya Conservatoire of Music Orchestra conducted by Levi Wataka, Cantus in Choro, Daniel Onyango and his band, and other solo\\/ensemble items by students and friends of the Conservatoire.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Date:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp; Saturday 3rd November 2012<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Venue:&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp; T<\\/strong><b>he Godown Arts Centre<\\/b> (L<b><i>ocated on Lusaka Road, off Dunga Road, Next to Car and General)<\\/i><\\/b><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Time:<b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7:00pm<\\/b>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Charges: <strong>Ksh. 300\\/-<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>You may download a copy of the program from the following link:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<a href=\\"\\/images\\/events\\/programs\\/Classics%20at%20the%20Go%20Down%20Draft%20Program.pdf\\">Download Concert Program Here <\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In case of queries, please contact:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>EVERLYNE KIRIMA<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>PROGRAMMES COORDINATOR<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\\">Tel: 0720962288\\/0737227903<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\\">Email: programmes@conservatoire.co.ke<\\/p>\\r\\n"}', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'classics at the godown', 'calendar/classics_at_the_godown/2012-11-03_19:00:00'),
(16, 'intro component', 5, '{"inTitle":"The Conservatoire","inImage":"<img src=\\"images\\/content\\/conservatoire_premises.jpg\\" alt=\\"The Kenya Conservatoire of Music premises\\" \\/>","inParagraph":"<h2>History of The Conservatoire<\\/h2>\\t\\r\\n<p>The Kenya Conservatoire of Music was founded in 1944 as The East Africa Conservatoire of Music. From a purely expatriate teaching staff and clientele, we have grown to a student base of over 400 students of all ages and backgrounds in Nairobi. We are a non-profit making institution with no religious or political affiliation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>About The Conservatoire<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Equipped with a staff of 15 highly qualified and committed teachers (both local and expatriate), our main focus is on ensuring that our students not only receive first quality training in music, but more importantly that they enjoy the practice and challenges of making music. The lessons are given both at our premises within the Kenya Cultural Centre, and at various schools that our teachers visit weekly. In total, we offer training to over three hundred students around Nairobi.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Our Mission<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Working to teach and promote good music of all styles in Kenya.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Our Vision<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>To ensure that every child has an opportunity to experience the benefits of learning to play\\/ sing music.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Our Curriculum<\\/h3>\\r\\n<p>Our curriculum caters for the musical needs of every individual while at all times ensuring that the skills acquired are measurable at international standards through examinations of the Associated Board of the Royal Schools of Music. We also cover all aspects of the IGCSE music curriculum.<\\/p>"}', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', NULL),
(17, 'content', 0, '"<h1>Teaching Rooms<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>We have 12 teaching rooms at <a href=\\"\\/facilities\\/cultural_centre\\">The Kenya Cultural Centre<\\/a> and 3 at <a href=\\"\\/facilities\\/godown\\">The GoDown Arts Centre<\\/a>, each sound proofed and equipped with a piano. The student is assured of a high quality learning environment.\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>Practice Rooms<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Our practice facilities include 3 teaching rooms at the KCC branch that double up as practice rooms and 3 that are at the GoDown Arts Centre. These are available for students to practice for one hour daily (Monday to Friday) at no charge, after having filled in a form to schedule their practice time. Non-students are not allowed to practice at the Conservatoire unless they are members of the Conservatoire. To become a member of the Conservatoire, one is required to pay an annual fee of Ksh. 1,200\\/-. The practice facilities can thereafter be availed once the practice form has been filled in. The practice rooms are managed strictly on a first come first served basis.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>Ballet \\/ Dance Studio<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Conservatoire is home to the Madame Vera Zerkovitz ballet studio. This ballet studio is suitable for small concerts and workshops and is also available for hire by other artistic groups for example modern dance and drama groups at Ksh. 2,000\\/- per hour. The studio is equipped with a piano, mirrors and washroom facilities.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>Hiring of Instruments<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many orchestral instruments are available to registered students, depending on their availability, for a hire fee of Ksh. 1,000\\/- per month. Saxophones, Tubas, Trumpets, Tromboned and Cellos are hired out at Ksh. 2,000\\/- per month. Pianos are hired out to students and non-students alike so long as the hire fees are paid. The hire fees are dependent on which type of piano is being rented out and the duration of the rental.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>The Library<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Located at the Go Down Branch, our library is well equipped with sheet music for all instruments and with audio recordings for student use as well as Music Literature for students of Music Theory and History. A registered student gains access to the library after paying a refundable deposit of Ksh. 2000 and a non-refundable access fee of Ksh. 1200\\/- per year. Registered members have a pay the access fee at a discounted rate of Ksh. 500\\/- per year. Please note that a student is not automatically a member of the Conservatoire, as highlighted in the schedule of fees.<\\/p>"', '', '2012-11-29 06:43:00', '2012-11-29 06:51:16', 'Teaching Rooms, Practice Rooms, Hiring of Instruments, The Library, Ballet / Dance Studio', NULL),
(18, 'component', 0, '"<p>All Fees are quoted in Kenya Shillings<br \\/>\\r\\nUnless otherwise quoted, all fees in the schedule below are non-refundable.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h1>Student Registration Fee<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">(Applicable to All New Students and Returning Alumni who have been away for two or more years)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">200\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h1>Lesson Fees<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Payable in advance (1 or 2 installments only)<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Individual Tuition (one-on-one lessons)<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">30 minute lessons (12 lessons at 900\\/-)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">10,800\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\">45 minute lessons (12 lessons at 1,350\\/-)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">16,200 \\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\">60 minute  lessons<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\"><\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left tabbed\\">Grade 8 level and below (12 lessons at 1,800\\/-)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">21,600\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left tabbed\\">Diploma Level (12 lessons at 2,500\\/-)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">30,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h2>Group Tuition:<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">Guitar Group Lessons<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">500\\/- per hour<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h1>Library Fees<\\/h1>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">Refundable Deposit (All Library Users)<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\"> 2,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\">Annual Fee for  Non-members (Non-refundable) <\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">1,200\\/- per annum<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\">Annual Fee for  Members (Non-refundable) <\\/td><td class=\\"right\\"> 500\\/- per annum <\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h1>Instrument Hire Fees<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><strong>Hire Fees<\\/strong> apply to all available instruments <strong>excluding Cellos, Tubas, Pianos and Saxophones<\\/strong>. All instruments <strong>(except pianos)<\\/strong> are rented to registered students only<\\/p>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\"> Refundable Deposit<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">5,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\">Fee Per Term<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">4,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h1>Fees for the Hire of the Ballet Studio<\\/h1>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\"> Refundable Deposit<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\"> 10,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td class=\\"left\\"> Fee per Hour<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\"> 2,000\\/-<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<a name=\\"other_fees\\"><h1>Other Fees<\\/h1><\\/a>\\r\\n<h2>Conservatoire Membership Subscription Fee<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">Conservatoire Membership Subscription Fee<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">1,200\\/- per annum<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<p>You will receive a membership card that entitles you to:\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\">\\r\\n<li>A free Calendar of Events for the year 2013<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Subsidized Ticket fees at all Concerts<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Subsidized Library Membership Fee<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Purchase selected Conservatoire products at a subsidized rate<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<span class=\\"italic\\">Please note that a student DOES NOT automatically become a member<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2>Orchestra Membership Subscription Fee<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">Orchestra Membership Subscription Fee<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">1,200\\/- per annum<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<h2>Ensemble Subscription Fee<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td class=\\"left\\">Ensemble Subscription Fee<\\/td><td class=\\"right\\">1,200\\/- per annum<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<p>(Conservatoire Children''s Choir, Kompl8 Vocal Octet, Conservatoire Senior Choir)<\\/p>"', '', '2013-01-14 00:00:00', '2013-01-14 00:00:00', 'fee structure', NULL),
(19, 'message', 0, '"<h1>Director''s Welcome Message<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div class=\\"pic-card\\">\\r\\n<div class=\\"img\\">\\r\\n<img src=\\"images\\/system\\/no-photo.png\\" alt=\\"no photo\\">\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<div class=\\"pic-details\\">\\r\\n<h2>Corrine Towett<\\/h2>\\r\\n<span class=\\"italic\\">Bachelor of Music, Dip. ABRSM - Conducting<\\/span>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<p>Equipped with a teaching staff of 28 highly qualified and committed teachers (both local and expatriate), the Conservatoire''s main focus is to ensuring that our students not only receive first quality training in music, but more importantly that they enjoy the practice and challenges of making music. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The lessons are given both at our premises within the Kenya Cultural Centre, at our Satellite Branch at the Go Down Arts Centre and at various schools that our teachers visit weekly. Every year, we offer training to an average of 400 students.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Conservatoire is a non-profit making institution with no religious or political affiliation.<\\/p>"', '', '2013-01-15 00:00:00', '2013-01-15 00:00:00', 'director''s message', NULL),
(20, 'content', 0, '"<h1>History<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The Kenya Conservatoire of Music was founded in 1944 as The East Africa Conservatoire of Music. From a purely expatriate teaching staff and clientele at its inception, the Conservatoire has grown to a student base of over 400 students of all ages and backgrounds in Nairobi. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h1>Mission and Vision<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Our Mission:<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Working to promote quality music education and the superior performance of music of all styles in Kenya.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Our Vision:<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>To ensure that every interested individual has an opportunity to experience the benefits of learning to make music.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h1>Governance<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The Director of the Conservatoire reports to The Conservatoire Council. The Council is composed of members from various professions who have a great appreciation for music and a passion for quality music education. The Council members voluntarily offer their time and management expertise and help keep the institution on track in the area of service delivery.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>The Conservatoire Council<\\/h2>\\r\\n<dl> \\r\\n<dt>Isaac O. Awuondo <\\/dt>&#09;<dd>- Chairman<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Atigala Luvai<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Betty Radier<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Christine Mutungi<\\/dt><dd>- Member <\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Fernanda da Gama Rose<\\/dt><dd>- Member <\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Francis Oludhe<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>James King''ara<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Katherine MacIntyre<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Valerie Kent<\\/dt><dd>- Member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Corrine Towett<\\/dt><dd>- Ex-Officio member<\\/dd>\\r\\n<\\/dl>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>The Administrative Team<\\/h2>\\r\\n<dl>\\r\\n<dt>Corrine Towett<\\/dt><dd>- Director<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Rosemary Kilonzi<\\/dt><dd>- Secretary<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>John Kahihu<\\/dt><dd>- Accountant<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Everlyne Wafula<\\/dt><dd>- Programmes Coordinator<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Seth Vosena Busolo<\\/dt><dd>- Support Staff<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>John Kinuthia<\\/dt><dd>- Support Staff<\\/dd>\\r\\n<dt>Margaret Bonareri<\\/dt><dd>- Support Staff<\\/dd>\\r\\n<\\/dl>"', '', '2013-01-15 00:00:00', '2013-01-15 00:00:00', 'about the Kenya Conservatoire of Music', NULL),
(21, 'content', 0, '"<p>To serve our increasing clientele, The Kenya Conservatoire of Music opened another teaching and learning facility at The GoDown Arts Centre in 2008. The GoDown is located on Dunga Road off Lusaka Road in South B, right after Car and General.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The location of this annex of The Conservatoire means that our clients in South B, South C, Nairobi West, Lang''ata, Embakassi no longer have to battle Nairobi traffic to get to their lessons.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Within this secure and spacious environment that is easily accessible to most Nairobians, you can get formal music instruction in singing, guitar, piano, drums as well as brand new practice facilities at very subsidized rates. This is a place for everyone, and form four leavers are especially encouraged to come in and \\"have a go\\" at unleashing their full musical potential.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Students will find very dedicated teachers to enable them to experience this once in a lifetime opportunity to learn a musical instrument. For more information about us and why we think music is vital for your child, please call us or simply visit us at the GoDown Arts Centre.<\\/p>\\r\\n "', '', '2013-01-21 12:00:00', '2013-03-08 05:00:00', 'Conservatoire at the GoDown', ''),
(22, 'content event', 0, '"<h1 class=\\"event_title\\">The Conservatoire Orchestra Concert<\\/h1>\\r\\n\\t<img class=\\"center\\" src=\\"\\/images\\/events\\/conservatoire_orchestra_concert-17-3-13.jpg\\" alt=\\"Conservatoire Orchestra Concert\\"\\/>\\r\\n\\t<p>The Combined Orchestras of the Conservatoire warmly welcome you to a grand celebration of enchanting music on Sunday, 17<sup>th<\\/sup> of March, 2013. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The lineup will include popular works from the field of classical music as well as performances of pieces of music composed or arranged by various Kenyan\\/Kenya-Affiliated composers, conducted by Levi Wataka and Corrine Towett:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Combined Orchestras<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td>William Tell Overture <\\/td>\\t<td>G. Rossini<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td>Radetzky March <\\/td>\\t<td> J. Strauss<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Symphony Orchestra <\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td>Valse Triste  \\t<\\/td>\\t\\t<td>J. Sibelius<\\/td><td><\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n\\r\\n<tr><td>Spring from \\"The Seasons\\" <\\/td>\\t<td>A. Vivaldi<\\/td>\\t<td>Soloist: David Ralak (First Movement only) <\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Prelude Orchestra<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td>Arab Dance from \\"The Nutcracker\\"<\\/td>\\t<td>Arr. Jeff Manookan<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td>Pomp and Circumstance<\\/td>\\t\\t<td>Arr. Jeff Manookan<\\/td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td>Theme from \\"Jupiter\\" <\\/td>\\t\\t<td>Arr. C. Towett<\\/td><\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Combined Orchestras, Group Guitar Class, Cantus in Choro and the Conservatoire Female Chorus<\\/h2>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><td>Conte Partiro<\\/td>\\t\\t\\t<td>F. Sartori<\\/td>\\t\\t<td>Performed by Nancy Day and Sylvester Makobi<td><\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr><td>For the Beauty of the earth<\\/td>\\t<td>J. Rutter<\\/td>\\t\\t<td>Performed by Conservatoire Female Chorus<\\/td><\\/tr><tr><td>Sarafina\\t<\\/td>\\t<td>Arr. J. Watatua<\\/td><td>Performed by 