(28, 'content event', 0, '"<a href=\\"http://www.conservatoire.co.ke/soul_itinerary\\">RESERVE THE SOUL KENYA 2013 TEAM<\\/a><p><\\/p><\\/br><img src=\\"\\/images\\/events\\/soul_kenya_2013.jpg\\" alt=\\"SOUL Kenya 2013\\" style=\\"width: 35%; display:inline-block;\\" \\/><div style=\\"width: 60%; display:inline-block; vertical-align: top;\\">\\r\\n<p><strong>Singers Of United Lands (SOUL)<\\/strong>&nbsp;is a <strong>non-profit<\\/strong> organization that was incorporated in 2002 in the United States of America, that seeks to <em>Develop International and Cultural Relationships through Vocal Music from around the World. <\\/em>S.O.U.L. is a unique quartet of four <strong>professional young adult singers<\\/strong> - each from a different country\\/continent.&nbsp; Every year&nbsp;a new team of four singers representing <strong>high-quality vocal musicianship, geographical diversity, and enthusiasm for sharing about their respective cultures<\\/strong>, is formed to share their native songs and cultures with schools and communities throughout the U.S. and beyond. They perform songs which are native to their home countries and give interactive workshops, presentations, performances, and lessons for audiences of all ages. All programming is conducted in English and features the four singers'' native songs and various aspects of their respective cultures.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In light of its mandate to promote the teaching and performance of excellent music of all styles in Kenya, the Conservatoire partnered with the SOUL program and introduced it in Kenya In 2012. The Group comprising of singers from India, Bolivia, Poland and Namibia had an African Tour that premiered in Kenya. For two weeks, the group visited a selected number of schools, colleges and other venues and interacted with the audiences, teaching various things about their native countries through workshops, songs and concerts. They then proceeded to do the same in Zambia and Zimbabwe.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The SOUL-Kenya 2013 chapter which features a Quartet comprising of singers from Guatemala, Philippines, Ireland and Russia who will visit various schools and institutions and offer workshops about their countries including lessons in language, geography, culture and music.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>All participants are required to pay a fee of Ksh. 300\\/- that will entitle them to workshop participation and free entrance to a concert that will be hosted by the SOUL Team on the 28th of April and 16th of May.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Check-out the <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/www.conservatoire.co.ke\\/soul_itinerary\\">SOUL-Kenya 2013 Itinerary<\\/a> to see when the team will visit an institution near you!!!<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div><p style=\\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.2;\\">We value your feedback. Share with us your experience with SOUL-Kenya.<\\/p>\\r\\n <div id=\\"disqus_thread\\"><\\/div>\\r\\n    <script type=\\"text\\/javascript\\">\\r\\n        \\/* * * CONFIGURATION VARIABLES: EDIT BEFORE PASTING INTO YOUR WEBPAGE * * *\\/\\r\\n        var disqus_shortname = ''kconserv''; \\/\\/ required: replace example with your forum shortname\\r\\n\\r\\n        \\/* * * DON''T EDIT BELOW THIS LINE * * *\\/\\r\\n        (function() {\\r\\n            var dsq = document.createElement(''script''); dsq.type = ''text\\/javascript''; dsq.async = true;\\r\\n            dsq.src = ''\\/\\/'' + disqus_shortname + ''.disqus.com\\/embed.js'';\\r\\n            (document.getElementsByTagName(''head'')[0] || document.getElementsByTagName(''body'')[0]).appendChild(dsq);\\r\\n        })();\\r\\n    <\\/script>\\r\\n    <noscript>Please enable JavaScript to view the <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/disqus.com\\/?ref_noscript\\">comments powered by Disqus.<\\/a><\\/noscript>\\r\\n    <a href=\\"http:\\/\\/disqus.com\\" class=\\"dsq-brlink\\">comments powered by <span class=\\"logo-disqus\\">Disqus<\\/span><\\/a>\\r\\n    "', '', '2013-04-10 00:00:00', '2013-04-10 00:00:00', 'SOUL-Kenya 2013 poster, introduction and write-up', NULL),
