(31, 'content event', 1, '{"evTitle":"Acoustic Alchemy","evImage":"class=\\"center\\" src=\\"*images\\/events\\/acousticalchemy_2013.jpg\\" alt=\\"Acoustic Alchemy\\"","evDate":"2013-06-02 18:30:00","evVenue":"Alliance Francaise","evTickets":"500 KShs Adults<br\\/>300 KShs Conservatoire Students and Children 12 Years and Below<br\\/>200 KShs Conservatoire Members","evDescription":"<p>In case of queries, please contact:<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>EVERLYNE KIRIMA<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>PROGRAMMES COORDINATOR<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\\">Tel: 0720962288\\/0737227903<\\/p>\\r\\n<p style=\\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\\">Email: programmes@conservatoire.co.ke<\\/p>\\r\\n"}', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Acoustic Alchemy', 'calendar/acoustic_alchemy/2013-06-02_18:30:00'),
(32, 'content component', 0, '"<p>Of all the forms of making music, singing has been the most fundamental mode of musical expression due to the fact that the body is the instrument and is accessible to most people. There is a notion that some people cannot sing, but this is a myth. The muscular requirements for singing are very similar to those for talking so technically if you can talk, then most likely you can sing. Perhaps the question is whether you can sing <strong class=\\"italic\\">well<\\/strong>.<\\/p><h1>Why Take Vocal Lessons?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>What marks out a good singer from an average one is down to how well they can control and manipulate their vocal chords. Some are endowed from early in life but for a majority, a lot of work needs to go into gaining this control. This is the purpose of taking voice lessons, training that enables one to manage and produce good sound quality that is in line with the kind of style of music being performed.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h1>What Does Vocal Training Entail?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Training entails systematic development of vocal technique as outlined below.<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\" type=\\"disc\\">\\r\\n<li>Introduction to the voice<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Preparing to sing and taking care of the voice<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Basic techniques in singing\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\">\\r\\n<li>Breathing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Pitching<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Articulation<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Expression<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Singing in Harmony\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\">\\r\\n<li>Voice placing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Voice balance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Voice Textures<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Repertoire\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\">\\r\\n<li>Analysis<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Genre<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>In addition to these vocal techniques modules designed to make one an all-round musician are included as follows:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul class=\\"bullets\\" >\\r\\n<li>Sight reading<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Aural training<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Basic Musicianship<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Performance etiquette<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<h1>What Genres of Music Do We Teach?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Just as with any kind of music different types of techniques are required. These are all offered in the institution, particularly classical singing, Jazz, Pop, Broadway and Contemporary styles.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h1>How Do We Assess Our Students?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>One can attain certificates in singing by taking the internationally recognised Associated Board of the Royal School of Music (ABRSM) examinations at different levels ranging from Preparatory stage to LRSM (equivalent to a Masters degree) in singing.<\\/p>"', '', '2013-06-25 00:00:00', '2013-06-25 00:00:00', 'VOCAL TRAINING, WHY TAKE VOICE LESSONS, SINGING, ABRSM VOICE or SINGING', NULL);
