(45, 'component', 7, '{"artTitle":"&ldquo;Random\\/Control&rdquo; Jazz Workshop","artTime":"2013-08-27 12:44:01","artAuthorAnchor":"Timothy Muritu","artParagraph":"\\n<img src=\\"\\/images\\/events\\/RandomControl.jpg\\">\\n<p>&ldquo;Random \\/ Control&rdquo;, an Austrian Jazz Band will host a Jazz Workshop on Saturday 7th September at 10am at the Kenya Conservatoire of Music Ballet Studio.<\\/p><p>The band consists of a trio of young professionals from the Vorarlberg region in Austria. All of the three artists are classically trained musicians and proficient in several instruments.The chief characteristic of &ldquo;Random \\/ Control&rdquo; is to quickly mix and switch instruments during their performances. They also recycle traditional Austrian folksongs by giving them a contemporary, funky edge.<\\/p>\\n<p>The Band leader David Helbock, at only 29 years, is one of the rising stars of modern jazz in Europe. An acclaimed jazz pianist and composer, he has already won a number of prices at several prestigious jazz festivals around Europe, including Montreux. This year, he is the opening act of the Jazz festival in Saalfelden, Austria. David has performed at the Goethe Institut in Nairobi in 2010 and is now returning to Nairobi with his band &ldquo;Random \\/ Control&rdquo;.<\\/p>\\n<p>Johannes B&auml;r and Andi Broger are renowned musicians in their own right: They perform together in a band called the &bdquo;Holstuonar Musig Big Band Club&ldquo;, a modern folk music group, which recently reached the top position in the Austrian pop music charts and is popular throughout German-speaking Europe.<\\/p>\\n<p>The instruments played by the trio include the following:<\\/p>\\n<p>David Helbock: Piano, Inside Piano, Electronics, Percussion, Voice, Composition<\\/p>\\n<p>Johannes B&auml;r: Trumpet, Trombone, Baritone, Tuba, Singing Tuba, Beat box, Helikon, Electronics, Percussion<\\/p>\\n<p>Andi Broger: Soprano sax, Alto sax, Tenor sax, Clarinet, Bass clarinet, Flute, Electronics, Percussion<\\/p>\\n<p>Entry to the Workshop is Free.<\\/p>\\n<p>If you are interested in participating in the workshop, kindly email the following details to programmes@conservatoire.co.ke on or before Thursday 5th September 2013:<\\/p>\\n<p>Name: <br \\/> Phone: <br \\/> Email: <br \\/> Instrument:<\\/p>","artReadMore":"<a href=\\"*noticeboard\\/random_control\\/2013-08-27_12:44:01\\">read more<\\/a>"}', '', '2013-08-27 12:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Random/Control Jazz Workshop', 'noticeboard/random_control/2013-08-27_12:44:01'),
