(51, 'component content', 0, '"<p>The Kenya Conservatoire of Music offers internationally recognized assessment through a partnership with the Associated Board of the Royal Schools of Music (ABRSM). The Conservatoire is the Kenyan representative for the ABRSM Practical Examinations. Over 1800 candidates enroll for these examinations in various instruments every year.<\\/p><p>The ABRSM route also provides Diploma options for selected subjects such as Conducting, Teaching and Performance. The Diplomas are offered in three levels:<dl><dt>DipABRSM<\\/dt> <dd>Equivalent to Undergraduate Degree Course &ndash; First Year<\\/dd><dt>LRSM<\\/dt><dd>Equivalent to Undergraduate Degree Course &ndash; Fourth Yeat<\\/dd><dt>FRSM<\\/dt><dd>Equivalent to a Masters Degree<\\/dd><\\/dl><p><a target=\\"blank()\\" href=\\"http://www.abrsm.org/\\">Find out More<\\/a><\\/p><h1>Why take a music exam?<\\/h1><p>&lsquo;Enjoyment through achievement&rsquo; is a phrase that sums up our philosophy, and earning an ABRSM certificate is a rewarding experience. If you are working hard to make progress with your music you need some way of recognising your success and reassurance that you are on the right road. This is exactly what music exams offer:<\\/p><ul class=\\"bullets\\"><li>motivation and inspiration, working from a carefully structured syllabus towards a definite goal<\\/li><li>a measure of personal progress and attainment against internationally recognised benchmarks<\\/li><li>an objective guide to improve your musical skills<\\/li><li>assessment by a respected and independent musician who has been highly trained and is constantly monitored<\\/li><li>sympathetic encouragement<\\/li><li>performance opportunities<\\/li><li>a real sense of achievement<\\/li><\\/ul><p>Of course, music exams do not suit everyone and exam syllabuses are not intended to provide a complete curriculum or choice of repertoire to the exclusion of all other music. All performers should explore a wide range of music to stimulate their interest and refresh their outlook.<\\/p><h3>Excerpt from &ldquo;These Music Exams&rdquo; by Clara Taylor<\\/h3><p>Download a Copy of <a href=\\"http://gb.abrsm.org/resources/theseMusicExams0607.pdf\\" target=\\"blank()\\">These Music Exams<\\/a><\\/p>"', '', '2013-09-16 11:02:04', '2013-09-16 11:02:04', '', NULL),
(52, 'component content', 0, '"<div id=\\"noticeboard\\" class=\\"kcmnews\\"><div class=\\"content_separator\\"><h1 class=\\"pageHeading\\"><a href=\\"/noticeboard\\">NoticeBoard<\\/a><\\/h1><\\/div><div id=\\"notice\\"><\\/div><\\/div><div id=\\"newsbulletin\\" class=\\"kcmnews\\"><div class=\\"content_separator\\"><h1 class=\\"pageHeading\\"><a href=\\"/news\\">NewsBulletin<\\/a><\\/h1><\\/div><div id=\\"news\\"><\\/div><\\/div>"', '', '2013-09-16 11:31:37', '2013-09-16 11:31:37', '', NULL),
(53, 'component', 0, '"<h1>COMPOSER TRAINING (PART ONE)<\\/h1>\\n<h3>TUTOR: JIM PYWELL<\\/h3>\\n<p><strong>Minimum Entrance Requirement:<\\/strong> Grade 3 Music Theory Certificate<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Minimum Age<\\/strong>: 16<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Dates:<\\/strong> 30<sup>th<\\/sup> September &ndash; 12<sup>th<\\/sup> October 2013<\\/p>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<td style=\\"text-align: center;\\" colspan=\\"2\\"><strong>Schedule of Classes<\\/strong><\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Monday 30<sup>th<\\/sup> Sep<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Thursday 3<sup>rd<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Saturday 5<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>9.00am &ndash; 12noon<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Monday 7<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Thursday 10<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Saturday 12<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>9.00am &ndash; 12noon<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/tbody>\\n<\\/table>\\n<p><strong>Total Hours of Classes:<\\/strong> 18<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Additional Time Recommended for Assignments:<\\/strong> minimum 10 hours of self-study time<br \\/><br \\/>This course is designed for people who want to start composing their own original music, with the eventual aim of writing for orchestra and other instrumental ensembles. Through listening, group discussions and practical tasks, it will explore techniques for experimentation to open your mind and generate musical ideas, and the craft of the composer including development and structuring of musical material. It will also include a basic introduction to techniques of writing for certain instruments. There will be regular assignments through the course which you&rsquo;ll be expected to present to the other students. Successful students may apply to be part of PART TWO which will run in December and January, and which will include the opportunity for student compositions to be tried out by players from the National Youth Orchestra of Kenya. Although the only entrance requirement is grade 3 music theory, a higher theory grade level and\\/or the ability to play a musical instrument will be to your advantage.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Space is limited to 25 participants<\\/h3>\\n<p><br \\/><strong>CHARGES: &nbsp; &nbsp;<\\/strong> <span style=\\"color: #333333;\\">COMPOSER TRAINING (PART ONE) (18 Hours) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ksh. 4,200\\/-<\\/span><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>About the Tutor:<\\/strong> Jim Pywell<br \\/><br \\/>The Charges include Tuition and Lesson Materials. Completion of the Courses will lead to the award of Individual Certificates and Reports. <br \\/><br \\/>50% Discount on Tuition Fee for Current Students of the Conservatoire who wish to enrol in any of the short courses above.<br \\/><br \\/>Participation in the Composer Training and\\/or Conductor Training courses may lead to the award of Credit and\\/or Exemptions for Undergraduate Music Courses that are offered by Universities affiliated to the Kenya Conservatoire of Music <br \\/><br \\/>Text books that may be required for study may be available at the Conservatoire Library and Bookshop. Library Membership is required for use of the Library.<\\/p>\\n<h1><br \\/>CONDUCTOR TRAINING (BEGINNER LEVEL)<\\/h1>\\n<h2>TUTOR: JIM PYWELL<\\/h2>\\n<p><br \\/><strong>Minimum Entrance Requirement:<\\/strong> Substantial ensemble experience as a singer and\\/or instrumentalist<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Minimum Age:<\\/strong> 16<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Dates:<\\/strong> 1<sup>st<\\/sup> &ndash; 11<sup>th<\\/sup> October 2013<\\/p>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<td style=\\"text-align: center;\\" colspan=\\"2\\"><strong>Schedule of Classes<\\/strong><\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Tuesday 1<sup>st<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Friday 4<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Tuesday 8<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Friday 11<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/tbody>\\n<\\/table>\\n<p><strong>Total Hours of Classes:<\\/strong> 12<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Additional Time Recommended for Assignments:<\\/strong> minimum 10 hours of self-study time and\\/or group work time<br \\/><br \\/>This course is designed for people who want to learn some basics about directing an ensemble, which may be vocal, instrumental, or a mixture of both. Through practical sessions, discussions and teamwork assignments, you will develop your practical techniques and also touch on a variety of other skills that are vital to running a musical group, such as planning, management, development of musicianship, self-evaluation, effective communication and presentation. You&rsquo;ll be expected to get together to work on assignments with other students outside of the taught class time.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Space is limited to 25 participants<\\/h3>\\n<p><strong>CHARGES:<\\/strong> &nbsp; &nbsp; <span style=\\"color: #333333;\\">CONDUCTOR TRAINING (BEGINNER LEVEL) (12 Hours)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ksh. 3,200\\/-<\\/span><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>About the Tutor:<\\/strong> Jim Pywell<br \\/><br \\/>The Charges include Tuition and Lesson Materials. Completion of the Courses will lead to the award of Individual Certificates and Reports. <br \\/><br \\/>50% Discount on Tuition Fee for Current Students of the Conservatoire who wish to enrol in any of the short courses above.<br \\/><br \\/>Participation in the Composer Training and\\/or Conductor Training courses may lead to the award of Credit and\\/or Exemptions for Undergraduate Music Courses that are offered by Universities affiliated to the Kenya Conservatoire of Music <br \\/><br \\/>Text books that may be required for study may be available at the Conservatoire Library and Bookshop. Library Membership is required for use of the Library.<br \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<h1>CREATIVE MUSICIANSHIP AND IMPROVISATION WORKSHOP<\\/h1>\\n<p><strong>Minimum Entrance Requirement:<\\/strong> at least grade 1 on an instrument or voice, but any grade level welcome<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Minimum Age:<\\/strong> 16<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Dates:<\\/strong> 5<sup>th<\\/sup> &ndash; 12<sup>th<\\/sup> October 2013<\\/p>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<td style=\\"text-align: center;\\" colspan=\\"2\\"><strong>Schedule of Workshop<\\/strong><\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Saturday 5<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>1.30pm &ndash; 4.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Sunday 6<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>2.00pm &ndash; 5.00pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Saturday 12<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>1.30pm &ndash; 4.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/tbody>\\n<\\/table>\\n<p><strong>Total Hours of Workshops:<\\/strong> 9<\\/p>\\n<p><strong>Additional Time Recommended:<\\/strong> minimum 10 hours of personal practice time and\\/or optional group work time<\\/p>\\n<p>This is a practical course for musicians of any level who wish to improve some of their overall musicianship skills. Whether your technical level is only being able to play a few scales and pieces, or whether you are more advanced, there are some things every musician can improve upon. Through a practical series of group workshops, you will have the opportunity to develop your skills in concentration, listening and responding, tone quality and articulation control, rhythmic coordination, dealing with nerves, and playing in tune with others. In combination with some regular practice you can also use the opportunity to gain new confidence, independence and agility on your instrument.<\\/p>\\n<p>Since the course operates most effectively with a mixed and balanced group, places may be limited for certain types of instrument if they are over-subscribed.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Space is limited to 20 participants<\\/h3>\\n<p><strong>Charges:<\\/strong> <span style=\\"color: #333333;\\">CREATIVE MUSICIANSHIP AND IMPROVISATION WORKSHOP (9 Hours)&nbsp;&nbsp; Ksh. 2,800\\/-<\\/span><\\/p>\\n<p><strong>About the Tutor:<\\/strong> Jim Pywell<br \\/><br \\/>The Charges include Tuition and Lesson Materials. Completion of the Courses will lead to the award of Individual Certificates and Reports. <br \\/><br \\/>50% Discount on Tuition Fee for Current Students of the Conservatoire who wish to enrol in any of the short courses above.<br \\/><br \\/>Participation in the Composer Training and\\/or Conductor Training courses may lead to the award of Credit and\\/or Exemptions for Undergraduate Music Courses that are offered by Universities affiliated to the Kenya Conservatoire of Music <br \\/><br \\/>Text books that may be required for study may be available at the Conservatoire Library and Bookshop. Library Membership is required for use of the Library.<br \\/>&nbsp;<\\/p>\\n<h1>CREATIVE MULTICULTURAL MUSIC WORKSHOP<\\/h1>\\n<p><strong>Minimum Entrance Requirement:<\\/strong> at least grade 1 on an instrument or voice, but any grade level welcome. Players of traditional Kenyan instruments especially welcome, no grade level required, but ability to play to at least basic technical level, either improvising or playing known traditional music.<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Minimum Age:<\\/strong> 16<br \\/><br \\/><strong>Dates:<\\/strong> 13<sup>th<\\/sup> &ndash; 15<sup>th<\\/sup> October 2013<\\/p>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<td style=\\"text-align: center;\\" colspan=\\"2\\"><strong>Schedule of Workshop<\\/strong><\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Sunday 13<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>2.00pm &ndash; 5.00pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Monday 14<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Tuesday 15<sup>th<\\/sup> Oct<\\/td>\\n<td>5.30pm &ndash; 8.30pm<\\/td>\\n<\\/tr>\\n<\\/tbody>\\n<\\/table>\\n<p>Total Hours of Workshops: 9<br \\/><br \\/>Additional Time Recommended: minimum 10 hours of personal practice time and\\/or optional group work time<br \\/><br \\/>This course is designed to explore new ground in creating music that crosses the boundaries between Western classical and traditional Kenyan music. It will consist of practical sessions involving experimental group work, listening and discussions, modelled initially on methods used by the group Kachumbari Seven several years ago. At the end of the course there may be an opportunity to showcase results or ideas-in-progress by inviting a small audience to the final session.<\\/p>\\n<h3>Space is limited to 20 participants<\\/h3>\\n<p><strong>Charges:<\\/strong> <span style=\\"color: #333333;\\">CREATIVE MULTICULTURAL MUSIC WORKSHOP&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;(9 Hours) Ksh. 2,800\\/-<\\/span><br \\/><br \\/><strong>About the Tutor:<\\/strong> Jim Pywell<br \\/><br \\/>The Charges include Tuition and Lesson Materials. Completion of the Courses will lead to the award of Individual Certificates and Reports. <br \\/><br \\/>50% Discount on Tuition Fee for Current Students of the Conservatoire who wish to enrol in any of the short courses above.<br \\/><br \\/>Participation in the Composer Training and\\/or Conductor Training courses may lead to the award of Credit and\\/or Exemptions for Undergraduate Music Courses that are offered by Universities affiliated to the Kenya Conservatoire of Music <br \\/><br \\/>Text books that may be required for study may be available at the Conservatoire Library and Bookshop. Library Membership is required for use of the Library.<\\/p>\\n<h1>NEW PROGRAMS AND COURSES COMING SOON TO THE CONSERVATOIRE<\\/h1>\\n<h3>COMPOSER TRAINING (PART TWO)<\\/h3>\\n<h3>CONDUCTOR TRAINING (INTERMEDIATE LEVEL)<\\/h3>\\n<h3>SING OUT! CHORAL TRAINING PROGRAM<\\/h3>\\n<p>Subscribe to our mailing list to receive updates on new courses, programs and upcoming events at the Kenya Conservatoire of Music<br \\/>&nbsp;<br \\/><br \\/><\\/p>"', '', '2012-11-29 06:35:09', '2012-11-29 06:35:09', 'short courses', NULL),
